article.description: High Point gets past UNC Greensboro 76-68
article.headline: High Point gets past UNC Greensboro 76-68
article.linkText: High Point gets past UNC Greensboro 76-68
article.story:
GREENSBORO, N.C. --  John Brown scored 24 points to lead High Point to a 76-68 win over UNC Greensboro on Monday night.

Devante Wallace and Lorenzo Cugini added 15 apiece for High Point (5-2). Brown hit 10 of his 12 free throw attempts as the Panthers made 84.8 percent (28 of 33) from the line compared to 9 of 15 for the Spartans.

Tevon Saddler made two free throws with 7:37 left to pull Greensboro within 54-51. But Wallace scored the next nine points -- on four free throws, a layup and a 3-pointer -- for a 63-51 lead.

UNC Greensboro (1-6) was paced by RJ White and Saddler with 14 each. Kayel Locke had 13 and Nicholas Paulos added 12. The Spartans were out-rebounded 33-25.

The game was tied early at 21 until High Point closed out the final 5:25 of the first half with a 14-6 run, highlighted by two Cugini 3-pointers.
